cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL

This paper is about meta-learning for deep neural net training, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The experiments conducted in the paper involve deep convolutional neural nets (cs.CV) and the datasets used are CIFAR10 and ILSVRC2012, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (cs.AI) in generating the damping and precondition matrix for the Hessian-Free approach. Finally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques (cs.CL) in the form of text-based datasets for meta-training the MLHF optimizer.
